Source.Name: mingw-w64-gcc
Source.Description: The GNU Compiler Collection includes front ends for C and C++, as well as libraries for these languages (libstdc++, libgcc,...). GCC was originally written as the compiler for the GNU operating system. The GNU system was developed to be 100% free software, free in the sense that it respects the user's freedom.
